caption: The anticipation is crazy as my wife and I are going there for our anniversary tonight.  I have experienced some of the best that Tampa has to offer and this is a place I have been wanting to go to for several years.  I would recommend this place to anyone I know.

The service was excellent. The atmosphere when you enter is a little cramped but enjoyable. Went with a party of friends ( 4 person party) and made reservations of course. Wine selection was admirable. We started off with a charcuterie board basically. Not at all what i thought it was going to be. Very bare board for the price. Nothing about what was on it explained like in most established restaurants. Sadly no pic of that which was honestly the worse part about the whole experience. The other dishes in my party were close to on point. Being a retired chef myself the dishes were in my opinion chef quality, aside from the lamb that I ordered. Although the meat was juicy and cooked to temp. ( mid rare) the method of which it was prepared and presentation was a little off. More of a new style look and no sear on the meat itself. The starch pairing ( sweet potato puree I would guess ) was tasty but not to my expectations for a lamb pairing. The mint/chime churri mixture was a nice touch and actually paired well sith the lamb. The other potatoes were on point. Would guess maybe the lamb was cooked as a rack then separated then broiled. Would like to give this establishment another try of course as the other dishes I sampled were of great quality. See a great deal of thought into this quaint upscale establishment.
Best Italian in Tampa
The food and service was excellent.
Great food and great service. Highly recommend.
Real italian food,great service and chef/owner cooks delicious!
Great food. Try the mushroom risotto! The fried artichoke was amazing as well. Tiramisu was unique, very sweet. Will be back!
Most amazing place! The food, beyond incredible. Will definitely be coming back! Amazing!

Oh my God!!! Another hidden gem...Get your reservation in! This place has flavor, class and some great drinks. I was blown away and shocked from the flavor...trust me you will not be let down with this as your option....

Small and intimate Italian restaurant . Everything from the bread to desert was delicious and perfectly presented. Customer service was great and the waitress was very attentive. This was my first time having risotto and it was nicely seasoned and creamy. The smaller portion is perfect for one person.

Phenomenal food and service awaits you at Cena. The entire experience is 5 Star all the way. Can't miss items include the Crispy Eggplant which may be the best single menu item I have had on 5 continents, burrata, and the redfish!

This is one of my favorite spots in my Channelside community to go for a nice dinner. Cozy atmosphere, welcoming staff and tasty food. The branzino, risotto, pasta bolognese and cheese selections are my favorites. They also have a good wine list and great specialty cocktails.
The food is incredible, and so is service. A perfect date night spot unique to Tampa.
Wonderful atmosphere, friendly staff, and incredible food. Very good best and wine selection. And the Grand Central property is hopping!
Nice dining experience.

The shrimp and scallop risotto, and the black truffle carbonara were also very good. But my definite favorite was the short rib risotto, delicious! My favorite spot for quality italian food. very savory. i had a brother come into town and he asked me to go back here. the bill was reasonable i would say. atmosphere is similar to a place in columbus i loved.

The place is good overall, but the last fish I had was so bad :( like nothing they described in the menu...black truffle carbonara - like mushy creamy pasta , that’s it.. something you make with source from Publix in microwave. I wold have never Published it if only I didn’t let them know how bad it was and I couldn’t even eat it and they just said I would let the chef know... ok than.. let him know and just please don’t order that!

Cheers for Cena  Five of us were celebrating a birthday and Cena was an excellent choice for dinner.  Service was very good and the place is welcoming and comfortable.  I do wish they had a list of house cocktails.  Apparently, that was 86’d because of covid.  But I had seen a list on their website and they were able to make a couple and they were excellent.  For appetizers we had the eggplant, the artichoke and the octopus salad.  All were delicious and the proportions were generous.  For entrees we had the Wagyu short rib, the Bolognese pasta, the lamb neck pasta and the bronzini fish.  Again, all were great—not a weak link in the bunch.  Same for the 3 desserts.  We enjoyed everything about our dinner and I would happily return.

What can you say about the best restaurant. Yummilicious! This restaurant has been able to combine historical favorites to the area with a interesting and flavorful twist. The eggplant was a after thought when we ordered. Now, we'll order it everytime were in Ybor City. Service was excellent and we loved the    location and menu selections. Both the oxtail (picture 1) and lamb neck (picture 2) was excellent. The tiramisu (picture 3) was something we've never seen but the creativity is where it counts. Lastly the appetizer was fried cheese with a jam. Salad that came was done amazing. Overall the food, we can tell was slow cooked to bring the flavor of herbs and spices. That's when you know, you can rely on restaurants like this to come back. I love to have an incredible dinner with my wife here occasionally. The Chef is quite talented and the service is spectacular. We walk down to this place and have a very intimate and romantic dinner regularly and we'll continue to do so for as long as they stay open. If they keep up the fantastic service, unbelievably delicious food, and professional and courteous atmosphere, they'll definitely stay on top of one of my favorite restaurants in Tampa. It's a small venue, probably 15 or  so tables. The owner or manager is usually walking around attentively and ensuring that everything is good, which is an understatement. Everything is fantastic! I had a very unique dessert there, a little twist on a tiramisu that was possibly one of the best desserts I've ever had. I am totally a food lover and have eaten all over the world, this place is in my top 10. Maybe top 5! Try them out, you will not regret your evening. (There's also a tiny little play-house theater next door for a different fun evening with your favorite dinner partner if you're looking for a nice evening.  Im not an employee there, I just love my romantic evenings with my wife.
Awesome

They told us to go outside and wait 10 minutes because they weren’t open yet.  Keep the door locked next time...? This place is amazing. Great service. The executive chef Michael buttacavoli is a great guy. Incredibly warm and welcoming atmosphere in the restaurant. Paul was an awesome bartender. Very attentive I never asked for a refill. Very good guy. Highly recommended.

Cozy atmosphere, great for a date or a gathering of a small group of friends. Lovely fresh Italian bread. Generous portions. A short but well chosen Italian wine list. Can have a charcuterie plate to share or a meal. Had the luscious potato and leek soup. Definitely good for the cold , bleak day that was happening. I had the branzino for my main and it was cooked perfectly. My date had the house salad and the rigatoni with the house Bolognese sauce and he enjoyed both. We both had wine, a red for him and a fruity Friugli white for me. Both complimented our respective meals well. We skipped dessert because we were full but all the choices looked good. We will return for more.
One of the best in Tampa!

I expected a lot after reading online reviews.  Cena is located in a trendy square set back from the road with other restaurants and bars. It’s just of a tram line so very handy from downtown.  The decor is modern, light and airy. As result this is not the place for a romantic dinner for two. It is also not very welcoming. Which was an off-putting start.  We hovered in the entrance looking lost (as did most other people) until someone noticed us from the back.  However, we did like our waiter and felt the service was overall good if a little understated (we would have ordered more drinks if someone had asked or come by the table).  The food was on the whole good, large portions, interesting combinations and well cooked.  Some odd decisions had crept onto the menu.  A beet salad that had way too few bits of beet, hardly any goat's cheese and way to much other stuff for example.  I ordered a veal chop. The veal was juicy and flavorful, the trimmings were less appetizing than they should have been.  The desserts were fun and just the right size. Avoid the olive oil cake at all costs it tasted old rubber tires. The flavor implied that the oil had been around way too long.  Despite all this, overall worth a try, but does not live up to its reputation.
Excellent food, excellent service.

This place is a small fancy establishment. You won't see white table cloths, but the menu is built from one chef and everything is expensive but perfect. The staff all around is nice and welcoming, with the food being very tasteful in every way. The plating is fancy and the place is always busy, so a recommended stop when downtown.

caption: What a great place for dinner. Paul, Joe and Michael were extremely welcoming and personable. Sunday night was half off wine bottles so we had a Primitivo blend that was excellent. We also had the crispy eggplant appetizer quite delicious. For dinner I order the puttanesca which was perfect. The style of the restaurant is like traditional Italian home with a touch of modern.

Amazing dining experience! We were greeted as soon as we came in by Joe, very fun and welcoming guy- let us know about the wine tastings they do every month. He was not our server, yet he consistently checked on us. Paul, our server, was very attentive, and Michael, the chef was extremely friendly! We were surprised that he personally brought our plates out and even conversed with us a bit. We had the crispy eggplant as our antipasto.. delicious! The bread was fantastic and having lived in Italy and marrying into a Sicilian family we have quite a bit to compare it to. Not only was the food outstanding, but so was the service and the friendly environment was just the cherry on top.  I recommend the house salad, very simple but very fresh and satisfying. Plus!! They have 1/2 priced wine bottles on Sundays! Very satisfied with our experience here. Sorry I hadn’t come before.
Love their Thursday wine nights!

The beef carpaccio was simple yet perfect, just a dash of salt and olive oil. The risotto was also delicious. Big risotto fan and I have never seen so many unique combinations before. It truest have you the feel of Grandmas sausage and peppers. Next time we visit Tampa we will be coming here for dinner.
Food was a little underwhelming

Can I give this a 4.5 stars? I don't quite feel that it merits the 5 stars it wants at this price point. Hands down, amazing Italian food. Elegant yet slightly casual atmosphere. Friendly or discreet service. It's probably the location in Channelside District, nestled between the high rise condos that give it a local corner feel so it's hard to give it a 5 star review, as I save those either for destination (stand alone/special occasion) restaurants or restaurants that exceed expectations of their price points.
Food and seevice was excellent. Perfect menu. There were 8 of us and the appetizers as well as the entrees were perfectly executed, This will be one of my favs!
I think the food is good but a bit more expensive than it should be.
The food was inventive while staying true to its Italian roots. the service was wonderful.

One thing that chefs struggle with is how do they stay true to their culinary heritage while still innovating? How far do they push the envelope, yet not lose the essence of a dish? This can be even more problematic with Italian food as many of the dishes and recipes are sacred! Well, Chef Michael Buttacavoli has found the sweet spot in this conundrum, and I don’t mean with just the delicious gelato! I visited Cena with my sister upon the recommendation of a friend, and the experience was extraordinary. From our host Joe (from Comack), to our server Marissa, all the way to speaking with Michael, who is not only a great chef, but a great guy! Cena has a great vibe, a bit old school, but also a bit industrial. Our meals were amazing, the menu is rotational, and always features in season ingredients; starting with the Antipasti and Insalata. I had the Octopus salad, which was spiced up with some Calabrian hot sauce and fried cauliflower. Now I’m a bit of an authority on octopus, having eaten my way across the Iberian Peninsula, where they hand out awards to the tapas bar that serves the best pulpo. The Cena version of this was fantastic, with some innovative surprises in flavor and texture.
Great food
Excellent service especially in regards to drink choices. A little on the expensive side, but the food is fantastic and the ambiance charming. Definitely great date and group event spot
Had dinner here last saturday,  really enjoyed the complex flavor of the Beef Involtini.  I will definitely dine here again!

In town for a quick birthday trip and we were craving some good Italian food nearby. Cena's did not disappoint! The food was so delicious and prepared so perfectly. Each bite was filled with so much flavor. Our server offered great recommendations for wine as well. Apart from the food, I will say the service and staff were just wonderful. We left about 30 minutes earlier than our reservation because we saw a storm rolling in, got there just after it began pouring, they sat us right away. A lot of the patrons were staying due to the weather and the staff made sure everyone was comfortable.

One thing that chefs struggle with is how do they stay true to their culinary heritage while still innovating? How far do they push the envelope, yet not lose the essence of a dish? This can be even more problematic with Italian food as many of the dishes and recipes are sacred! Well, Chef Michael Buttacavoli has found the sweet spot in this conundrum, and I don’t mean with just the delicious gelato! I visited Cena with my wife upon the recommendation of a friend, and the experience was extraordinary. From our host Joe (from Comack), to our server Marissa, all the way to speaking with Michael, who is not only a great chef, but a great guy! Cena has a great vibe, a bit old school, but also a bit industrial. Our meals were amazing, the menu is rotational, and always features in season ingredients; starting with the Antipasti and Insalata.  I had the Octopus salad, which was spiced up with some Calabrian hot sauce and fried cauliflower.  Now I’m a bit of an authority on octopus, having eaten my way across the Iberian Peninsula, where they hand out awards to the tapas bar that serves the best pulpo. The Cena version of this was fantastic, with some innovative surprises in flavor and texture.  My wife had the baby kale Cesar; the chickpea croutons were an awesome touch! And Michael is not afraid to use anchovies to keep it authentic.  We had the gnocchi for a pasta course, which was equally inventive as the octopus.  The tomato sauce included braised oxtail, again a combination you’ll not find almost anywhere! The gnocchi had a finishing touch of being lightly braised in the skillet, which gave it an even deeper flavor and texture. Absolutely delicious. My secondi was the Parmesan crusted halibut, which was seared to perfection with a fabulous faro and risotto.  Again, another twist on a theme, but next level in flavor! This superb meal was finished off with gelato and of course, some house made limoncello! In addition to my Iberian escapade, my wife and I recently made a trip to Sicily, where needless to say food is a way of life. I would put the meal at Cena on this level. Plus not only is the food exceptional, it is an exceptional value!  They are transitioning to a new menu as I type this so get to Cena and have the best of the old AND new world!
Micheal is a great chef. I love eating here.
This restaurant is OUTSTANDING from the wine, bread and olive oil to the  small plates...can't wait to go back.
Ok location for italian food. I was super full. It has a nice feel to it. Feels like a place in Charlotte that I enjoyed visiting.
Chef Mike, Paul, and Joe. Best team around. Every time we come it’s a fantastic experience. Excited to see the new menu coming soon. Thanks guys
Thank you for always being creative with the delicious food and the environment for us to enjoy. Cheers.

We celebrated our 35th wedding anniversary at Cena. We recently moved from NY/NJ so food is our specialty. This eggplant appetizer is to die for!! So different than any thing I have had. That tomato jam really sealed the deal. My drink for the night was the Mule, very good and gingery l. My husband and I had the shrimp, scallops risotto, risotto is well seasoned and scallops and shrimp had just enough color on it and very tender. We had to chocolate chip cannoli to go (we ate the later, yummy) I would definitely return again and again and this time no sharing that eggplant! Thanks again Joe!
Amazing food, ambiance and staff! If you are looking for authentic yet contemporary menu, Chef Mike ROCKS! Joe, the manager is very attentive and personable. Highly recommended Cena!
Great service, delicious food.

My wife and I have enjoyed this spot numerous times by ourselves and family. The menu hasn't changed much since the last time we dined. I did notice a beautiful interior refresh. I really enjoyed the crispy eggplant and the truffled mac with peas was perfect! Our server, Margarita, was amazing!
Food is absolutely wonderful!! Chef Butta creates fantastic unique dishes with amazong flavors. You will not be disappointed.

This should get a 10/5 stars. The restaurant offers an intamate friendly environment, Paul the bartender was fantastic, every dish that we ordered just seemed to get better and better. The meatball antipasto was fantastic.The rustic bolognese was my husbands favorite. The shrimp and scallop risotto was my favorite.  Their take on the tiramisu was like nothing I’ve seen before and was absolutely every bit as good as it looked. Hands down best Italian food in Tampa.
Great little gem in downtown Tampa! Delicious food and top notch service in a contemporary atmosphere. Highly recommend!
Delicious! Always a great meal.

Our large group ate at Cena after attending Stageworks on a Sunday in December. Service was slow, even though we had made reservations for our 30 or so people. The menu was all a la carte and very limited. For just a salad and seafood ris. and a glass of the house rose, my tab came to $35 plus tax and the mandatory 20% tip. Oh, and they were out of the item I first requested, which the waiter should have mentioned when he passed out the menus. My meal was adequate , nothing special. One in our party was very disappointed in the beet salad he had. No one was thrilled with their meal. I don't consider this place worth my time and money, so I won't be back.  Maybe Mr. Vinick can afford their prices and put up with the lack of choices, but I will not.

Amazing experience. We were in from out of town and looking for a nice evening, and Cena delivered. Delicious food with a good number of options, creative cocktails, and a cozy vibe. Exactly what we were looking for.

(I HAVE A NEW RESPONSE BELOW THIS 11/19/2018)   Went to dinner here. Being a sophomore food connoisseur eating at many different establishments. Was questioned if I had reservations. No, I didn't. Was surprised to see others were sat down promptly without being asked the same. My wife noticed that the server delivered bread to the two new guests that were just seated, after us. However we didn't receive the same. Menu said another order of bread was $2, when the complimentary ones never made it. Paid too much for a bone in rib eye, that is served to you medium rare without asking you what temperature you desire. My wife excused herself to the restroom, but returned immediately. She couldn't use it being there were cockroaches already occupying the females restroom. Cockroaches?? at this high dollar, reservation based restaurant with views of favoritism towards different customers? What a mistake! Never Again!!!  Thank you for your response. I posted that review January 14, 2018. And you replied 2 days ago. "Your establishment" response? Are you the new management that has cleaned up the bathroom roach infestation? Did you give customers the choice of deciding the temperature of how they wanted their steak prepared? Did you tell your employees to not ask Hispanic people if they have reservations? Did you explain to your employees to bring water to the Hispanic customers? Did you explain to your employees to ask EVERYONE if they have reservations, and not promptly sit others down? I didn't want to make this review "Race" related as you've read the existing post. At the end of the day, Money is green. It has no preference. For you to tell me...how my lies don't seem too appealing but you thank me for my honesty, is a slap in my face! I can't make this up towards my experience at your restaurant "Cena". I don't just make up reviews. I write to exactly what happened in the events of "your establishment". Read the rest of my reviews. I have no reason to make false review or representation. I want you to know that I will NEVER show my presence at "Cena, your establishment ", even if it was FREE and you gave me extra gift cards to take home. I speak TRUTH in my experience and I'm sorry you don't have dignity to accept it. I have no reason to lie!

The food is consistently amazing - So good that I had my wedding rehearsal dinner at Cena. Love Chef Mike and the entire Cena crew!

This was my first time and I was very impressed. The food is delicious; I had the eggplant appetizer and the small portion of chicken cacciatore risotto. Even their small portion option was ample! The restaurant has a chic, but comfortable, style. Flora, our waitress, was excellent. Don't leave without trying to tiramisu- decadent and beautifully presented.

I eat here so often since I live nearby. Simply speaking, delicious food, well decorated dishes, and friendly service.  It's a great place, with brilliant cocktails. The food is tasty, hearty, but not heavy with imaginative use of vegetables. Crispy eggplant with truffle cheese, fried olives, meatball with braised collard greens, buratta salad, wild mushrooms risotto, crispy pork cheek, oxtail gnocchi, all kinds of fish, wonderfully light tiramisu, ridiculously delicious banana trifle-- are all some of my favorites.  I would spend most of the meals rhapsodizing over the food; I have to imagine that this is a good sign.

The food here is incredible! We went with a group of friends, and shared several plates - they were all amazing. This is a great spot and everyone who likes Italian should make this a must try. Its in the channel side area of Tampa, so its in an area where you can walk around and check things out and walk off your food.
Remarkable food and service. Have visited many times and love everything. Great menu, and wonderful wine choices. A downtown gem!
Food is delicious! Great customer service.
Really like the place. Great for a date.
Great food, great service, prefect portions

One of the best Italian places here in Tampa. Prices are slightly above average but it is a great price for the quality and taste of the food! I absolutely love their babe kale Cesar salad with chickpea croutons. They also have a great wine selection and have a monthly wine tasting! Very nice calm atmosphere a great place for a date or taking a client to close on a deal!
Nice food

Cena is a lovely spot in the Channelside district.  The burrata salad was the best I've ever had, and the eggplant fonduta for this non-eggplant lover was excellent.  I went again this week and shared the oxtail pasta with friends and we all enjoyed it.  It's a convenient choice if you're going to Stageworks theater next door, and the parking garage is free for the first hour or 2.

The drinks are unique and delicious. It's a place you can spend hours at and not realize. The service is suberb and extremely helpful. I didn't try the food but after the drinks and desserts, there is no doubt that it will be spectacular.
Very upscale in every way.
Would have given them 5 stars, but only teas they had were English Breakfast, Green, and a fruit herbal for after dinner.
The food was art on a plate
The food was amazing. Can't believe we didn't find this gem in Channelside earlier.
Top of the Mark for one Chefs interpretation of Italian. Great bar cocktails ( get that one made with house barrel aged liquor). Service spot on with Eric. Hats off, we'll be back
First time here and it was excellent! Service and food was amazing! Remodel looks good. Paul was a very good bartender!
One of a kind delightful cuisine and wonderful one of a kind Ambiance and service to match in tampas beautiful Channel District!!
username: Jennifer Brewer Org. MavenMarket Tampa Collabs

caption: Best restaurant in the City. Great food! Great chefs! Great sweets!!
Met some friends there that were in town from England and had a wonderful time. The staff was great and the food was amazing.

Two stars because the food and bartenders are GREAT. However,  the manager is pompous and condescending. After being loyal customers for two years, the manager offended us terribly. As someone who works in customer service, a word to the wise; you cannot pick and choose who you offer a stellar customer experience to. At this price point, one can go to one of Tampa's Italian eateries with STELLAR service, and no fear of receiving the sleight because you are not with the "in crowd" that evening. We will be giving our business to an establishment that respects its clientele.
Good cocktails and food.
Excellent high end Italian cuisine . Chef Michael makes fantastic food. Paul the bartender makes great cocktails.  The tiramisu is a must try.
Delicious, with top-notch service, highly recommended.
Outstanding. Chef Michael has the right stuff. We needed a 5 star restaurant in the Tampa Bay and we now have one.
I work around cena they are very nice and clean people i love the restaurant my self.
Nice place with good ambiance and good food.
WONDERFUL desserts
Very nice experience after a play next door at Stage Works theater.  Eggplant appetizer was great, as were main dishes.  House red was delicious and a bargain.

This was a really great experience, and I will definitely go here again. The food was all excellent, and the service was too. The reason I can't give it 5 stars is the hugely limited menu and wine selection. And there's a $20 charge if you bring your own wine.

We had a chance to finally check out Cena last night. Everything about the restaurant, from the management, to the servers, and let's not forget the chef and the food, was impeccable. The staff is very warm and welcoming, and made you feel at home. We had the roasted eggplant and burrata as appetizers, gnocchi and classic bolognese for main course, and the carrot cake with some espresso to top things off. The carrot cake cannot be expressed in words. You have to see it, and devour it. We just came back from a two month trip to Europe where we spent a solid three weeks in Italy. Cena's food is at par, if not better, than some of the best restaurants we experienced in the motherland. We already made our second reservation and look forward to many more.

Great place.  We at at the bar.  Really liked the kale Cesar salad - chickpea croutons were a creative surprise.   We had shrimp carbonara which was also very good.  Carrot cake stole the show though.  It's a must try!
Ask for Joe. He'll guide you to the right dish.

What an amazing find tucked away in Channelside.  The staff was amazing, the food was great and the atmosphere was spot on for a great night out.  If you haven't been to Cena yet, make it your next night out.
One of my favorite restaurants.  Local bread and unique selection of wines.  Menu is always updating.
Food was excellent. Must get bar service figured out. Missing some Premium liquors that people like. Mixers were way below average.
Good food, great service!  Nice courtyard for outside seating
We go every year at our anniversary. We are never disappointed and have a lovely dinner every time.
Great place, service was good.  Not my style on donning.
Good Risotto.
Save room for dessert.

Went to Cena for the first time before attending the Game of Thrones Orchestra at the Amalie Arena. The bartenders joyful demeanor and playful humor really added to our evening. We asked so many questions and he answered them l politely and with detail. Really helpful! The atmosphere is a mix between upscale bar and white table cloth. So dress comfortable/fancy if that makes any sense lol.  We had the buratta salad as an appetizer. They also serve complimentary bread with oil and balsamic vinegar. Very good as far as pre mela bread goes. Hot, crunchy on outside and soft on the inside. For dinner we had their braised beef in a red sauce and the seafood risotto. The braised beef was delicious but the seafood risotto stole the show. If you like risotto or have never had it start here. They are known for their risottos and I can see why!  We will be coming back for dessert and more risotto!
Sea food dishes were outstanding. Pasta was made to perfection.Service was excellent.Great job. Keep it up
Amazing food and service.
Finest Italian cuisine in the area.Great sea food and delicious pastas and salads.We thoroughly enjoyed our food.
Best Cheese experience ever. The honey cone cheese, yummy! Very special place for me.

Celebrated my wife's best friends' birthday here.  Food was incredible, very intimate ambiance , service was friendly and first class and found perfect balance on checking in on us, but letting us enjoy private time.  Highly recommend the Risotto seafood dish and we enjoyed several of their desserts.

Cena Italian Restaurant offers classy upscale dining in the downtown Tampa channelside area. I liked their shrimp pasta with scallops and their chicken marsala. A little more expensive than average at $25-$30 per plate.  Nice for special occasions but not a regular spot. Not open for lunch. Only open for dinner.

Watched the dirty shaggy Chef smoke a cigarette out next to the dumpster on the side of the building as my girlfriend and I walked up for a fine dining experience.  Food was really heavy and dense. EXTREMELY flavorful but after a few bites was tired of it.  Theres much better elsewhere.  I can recommend to try but not regularly.

The service was absolutely subpar with the elegance they attempt to exude.  I called the night before to make my reservation and preordered a desert with a candle, as we were celebrating my friend's birthday---I wanted to surprise her. They never brought it out.  Our table ordered theBeer Glazed Pork Belly and the Crispy Eggplant appetizers. Both were well prepared and tasted divine. Unfortunately that's where the culinary excitement ended. My friend and I both order risotto dishes. They BUTCHERED them. The consistency of the risotto was more en par with sticky rice. AND they served them on cold plates! How does an Italian restaurant not know how to prepare one of the most basic Italian dishes?  Suffice it to say, I was left quite disappointed.
The food and atmosphere are wonderful. Portions are perfect and the service excellent. Can't wait to go back!
Brought my wife there on our anniversary. What a great experience we had, from the awesome food as well as 5 star service. Would recommend it to everyone.
Had a good experience here.  Nice atmosphere, and a great staff added to the night.  Meals and appetizers were prompt and tasty, and the portions were just right.

Parking can be a bit of a challenge but it is worth the struggle. Unfortunately, our first visit to Cena was not the best service experience. We had to make sure our server knew we wanted an appetizer, remind her to bring silverware when she brought out our entrees, remind her to pick up the tab with our credit card sitting right in front of her on the table and she never served us with complimentary bread. A sub par service event at best.  However, she was friendly and courteous just think she was a bit scatter brained.  The food, however, the food was good. Portion sizes are more European, meaning on the smaller side but they were adequate. The food was tasty and all the flavors complemented each other with unique combinations. When our meals arrived the  plates where served a bit cooler than they should have been and might have been sitting a bit too long before service.  The ambiance is a bit too sterile and clinical feeling for me and the interior walls of concrete and high ceilings give it a very hollow sound.  Overall the experience was good and the service just a below average.
Great place to dine....food is excellent the staff is Friendly! Atmosphere is welcoming just an overall top notch experience Chef Michael has a great team.
BEST Tiramisu EVER!

The food was fabulous, server was friendly and attentive but not overly so (I really don't like when servers hover), and the atmosphere was really nice even with a food truck rally going on outside. Went for a friend's birthday and we all split the entire dessert menu as well as the full platter of cheese and charcuterie which was excellent. Husband and I shared (but didn't get it split or a spare plate to avoid a split fee) a pheasant pasta dish that was phenomenal as well as a prosciutto and endive salad. Our bottle of house wine was presented to us like it might be the finest wine on the menu which was nice. The cookie butter cone with chocolate gelato was to die for. Overall it was pricey, but we left full and completely satisfied. Definitely would go back.
Had Jen B as our server. Very rude and poor service. The menu is not understandable and the food was not good. The ambience and location are great.
Just go there! Nothing I had was bad and the service was fantastic!

My wife and I went to Cena on July 4th. We were very fortunate to find this eatery as we are out of the area. The food was masterfully creative and one of the best dining experiences we have had in Florida. Marissa was our waitress and she was superb. It you are a bar food person this experience is not for you.

Wow!  We have been going to Cena since they opened and they've always been great! When we saw their flyer for Thanksgiving to go it was a no-brainer.  Holy cow did they ever outdo themselves !!  The turkey was full, juicy and boneless breasts with the dark meat deboned all with a bed of excellent sausage dressing.  The sides were unbelievable as well!  All gourmet.  The perfect mix of quality and quantity.  Hats off to Chef Michael and the rest of the folks at Cena!  I don't know how you guys pulled off such a great meal for so many.  It's great to have such a professional staff so close!  Christmas meal is already planned !!  Thanks!

Very disappointing. Pasta dishes were very small portions. The spaghetti and Italian sausage was not spaghetti served with Italian sausage but rather spaghetti served with a sausage meat sauce.  The chicken Marsala was good. Overall the food flavorful but nothing impressive and overpriced. (They even charged us a sharing fee for splitting a salad!) There were 4 in our party and none of us would go back.

This place is so damn good.  Very traditional, extremely good service (felt like I knew the server for years), cool location (inside and out), and the Risotto with the mushrooms puts any place in NY on blast!  My mom goes all time, and so do I!  Thanks Chef Mike, you are so great!

This place is a foodie's delight.  From apps to desert everyone kept talking about how good the food was.  I had the braised short rib pasta and it was a great twist on a traditional dish.  I felt the prices were very reasonable for what we got.  Parking was free since we were there less than 2 hours.  (Note that google maps takes you to the wrong place)

I've dined at Cena twice in the past two months, and I've been thoroughly delighted both times. The food is modern Italian, and is at once both rustic and refined. The attention to detail in flavor speaks clearly for what a restaurant can be when the chef is in charge.  Being Italian and loving Italian food, I have an ingrained view of what an average Italian restaurant will look like and how the experience will go. Italy and the "old world" are beautiful, but I do not need to be magically transported there every time I want to eat Italian food. Thankfully, none of my stereotypes were accurate at Cena. The decor is modern, minimal, and somewhat industrial, yet oddly warm and welcoming. In a word - clean.  Chef Mike introduced himself as the owner and I noticed him visit all of the tables in the dining room at some point during our dinner. I have a service background, and seeing the chef (even as an owner) do this makes me feel a lot better about the food I'm eating. The menu appears to be constantly evolving based on my two visits. The menu items seem to change with what ingredients are available - tragic if you're craving a specific dish, but also reassuring as a food lover, since you'll never be served sub-par ingredients. We were told the menu also changes with the seasons and based on popularity of dishes, which I'm happy about simply to try new creations from this chef.  The wine selection is all Italian, which I wasn't crazy about but hey - it's an Italian restaurant so what can I complain about. Low to mid range Italian wine is forgettable in my opinion, while high end Italians are unparalleled. Thankfully there was a fantastic big, bold red available without a Sassicaia pricetag. I can't remember the name, but it started with a "B" and had a lot of alliteration in the name. The bartender will know which one. Order that wine.  Speaking of the bartender and service in general: We only ever dined at the bar, so we cannot speak for any of the table service. Our bartender was great, knowledgeable, and friendly. Though the restaurant was new on our first visit and he did not know everything about everything, which can be forgiven as he quickly found out any question we asked - and we ask a lot of questions. The reason I wouldn't give the service a perfect score was that they seemed to be learning still, though they were fast and attentive so we were never disappointed. We spoke to some other guests who were frequent diners and they felt the same way about the service, though they mentioned they've seen constant improvement over the few months they've been open.  Overall our experiences here were excellent and we'll be back anytime we're in Channelside. The portions are the right size, the price is great considering the quality and ingenuity, the flavors are just fantastic, the restaurant itself is modern and clean, and the staff is quick, pleasant, and informed. Places like this are what Tampa needs more of, in my long-winded and humble opinion.
